FBIS4-9725 "drlat063_c_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-063 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 MEXICO PPS, PDM Hope Zedillo `Will Stick' to Agreements PPS, PDM Hope Zedillo `Will Stick' to Agreements PA3103171094 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 31 Mar 94 PA3103171094 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 31 Mar 94 Spanish BFN [From the "Early Morning" newscast] [Text] At the time they welcomed Ernesto Zedillo into the electoral campaign as PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] presidential candidate, the Socialist People's Party [PPS] and the Mexican Democratic Party [PDM] said they hope Zedillo will stick to the agreements signed by Luis Donaldo Colosio. [Begin recording] [PPS Deputy Leader Cuauthemoc Amezcua] We hope he will make a great and responsible effort to follow up and fulfill the democratic agreements signed by eight political parties. [PDM President Marcelo Gaxiola] Dr. Zedillo's taking up Colosio's banner and making a public commitment to follow the same course should be hailed and regarded as positive. [end recording] Both the PPS and PDM coincided by saying evidently, the new PRI candidate is at a disadvantage in relation to the other candidates and that, for this reason, he must make a greater effort to catch up and recover lost time.
